  {"id":"g10-l4-reading-001","grade":10,"lesson":4,"lessonTitle":"Traveling the World","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"First Trip Abroad\n\nLast summer, Neda traveled outside Iran for the first time. She was excited but also a little nervous. Before the trip, she read about the culture and customs of the country she was visiting. At the airport, she had to show her passport and answer a few questions. During her stay, she visited many historical attractions and tried local food. The people there were very hospitable, and they were happy to answer her questions about their city. Neda bought small souvenirs for her family and friends. When she came home, she said it was the best journey of her life.","prompt":"What did Neda do before her trip?","options":["she learned to cook","she bought a car","she read about the culture"],"answer":"she read about the culture","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l4-reading-002","grade":10,"lesson":4,"lessonTitle":"Traveling the World","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"First Trip Abroad\n\nLast summer, Neda traveled outside Iran for the first time. She was excited but also a little nervous. Before the trip, she read about the culture and customs of the country she was visiting. At the airport, she had to show her passport and answer a few questions. During her stay, she visited many historical attractions and tried local food. The people there were very hospitable, and they were happy to answer her questions about their city. Neda bought small souvenirs for her family and friends. When she came home, she said it was the best journey of her life.","prompt":"Neda didn't need to show her passport at the airport.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
