  {"id":"g10-l4-reading-006","grade":10,"lesson":4,"lessonTitle":"Traveling the World","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"Travel Rules\n\nEvery country has its own travel rules. Travelers must carry a valid passport, and some countries also require a visa. At the airport, passengers should arrive early and follow the safety instructions carefully. Travelers must not carry dangerous items in their bags. They should also learn a few basic rules about the local culture before they arrive. For example, in some countries, tourists must dress modestly when they visit religious places. Following these simple rules can make any trip safer and more enjoyable.","prompt":"What must travelers carry?","options":["extra money","a valid passport","a map"],"answer":"a valid passport","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l4-reading-007","grade":10,"lesson":4,"lessonTitle":"Traveling the World","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"tf","style":"konkur","passage":"Travel Rules\n\nEvery country has its own travel rules. Travelers must carry a valid passport, and some countries also require a visa. At the airport, passengers should arrive early and follow the safety instructions carefully. Travelers must not carry dangerous items in their bags. They should also learn a few basic rules about the local culture before they arrive. For example, in some countries, tourists must dress modestly when they visit religious places. Following these simple rules can make any trip safer and more enjoyable.","prompt":"Travelers can carry dangerous items in their bags.","options":["True","False"],"answer":"False","difficulty":"medium"},
  {"id":"g10-l4-reading-008","grade":10,"lesson":4,"lessonTitle":"Traveling the World","section":"reading","grammarPoint":null,"format":"mcq","style":"konkur","passage":"Travel Rules\n\nEvery country has its own travel rules. Travelers must carry a valid passport, and some countries also require a visa. At the airport, passengers should arrive early and follow the safety instructions carefully. Travelers must not carry dangerous items in their bags. They should also learn a few basic rules about the local culture before they arrive. For example, in some countries, tourists must dress modestly when they visit religious places. Following these simple rules can make any trip safer and more enjoyable.","prompt":"What should travelers do before they arrive?","options":["buy new clothes","call the embassy","learn basic cultural rules"],"answer":"learn basic cultural rules","difficulty":"medium"},
